<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>WVU Earns Fourth FWAA “Super 11” Honor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/football-wvu-earns-fourth-fwaa-super-11-honor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/football-wvu-earns-fourth-fwaa-super-11-honor</guid><category>Football, Athletics Communications</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2025-Super11" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" /><br /><br />DALLAS – One first-time winner and 10 previous ones, including West Virginia University for the second time in a row and fourth time in the past six years, comprise the 17th Super 11 Awards, presented annually by the Football Writers Association of America to the best performing College Sports Communicators departments in the NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision. The awards announced this week are for the 2025 season.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG"><media:title>2025-Super11</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/Super11_16x9.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 9 Apr 2026 12:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58981</s:story_id></item><item><title>Date Set for WVU, Wake Forest in Greensboro</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/mens-basketball-date-set-for-wvu-wake-forest-in-greensboro</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/9/mens-basketball-date-set-for-wvu-wake-forest-in-greensboro</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Wake" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/9/wake.jpg" /><br /><br />Princeton, N.J. – The Gazelle Group is pleased to announce the 2026 edition of Holiday Hoopfest presented by Visit Greensboro featuring Wake Forest and West Virginia. The Demon Deacons and Mountaineers will compete on Saturday, December 19, 2026 at First Horizon Coliseum in Greensboro, North Carolina.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/wake.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/wake.jpg"><media:title>Wake</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/9/wake.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 9 Apr 2026 11:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58980</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Cruise to Victory Over Marshall</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/baseball-mountaineers-cruise-to-victory-over-marshall</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/baseball-mountaineers-cruise-to-victory-over-marshall</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ian Korn" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team earned its second win this season against in-state rival Marshall with a 12-2 victory in eight innings, Wednesday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 22-7 while the Thundering Herd fall to 14-17.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg"><media:title>Ian Korn</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/20260329_MOC_RiverhoundsvSDportingJax_TT-01392-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 8 Apr 2026 23:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58979</s:story_id></item><item><title>Sixth Mountaineer Gear Sale to Take Place at Gold-Blue Spring Festival</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/football-sixth-mountaineer-gear-sale-to-take-place-at-gold-blue-spring-festival</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/football-sixth-mountaineer-gear-sale-to-take-place-at-gold-blue-spring-festival</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Mountaineer-Gear-Sale" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/8/852083108-fb26_gearsale_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. - The West Virginia University Athletics Department will conduct its sixth Mountaineer gear sale on Saturday, April 18, as part of the Gold-Blue Spring Festival from 9:30 a.m. – 11:30 a.m., in the Diversified Energy Terrace club area of Milan Puskar Stadium.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/852083108-fb26_gearsale_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/852083108-fb26_gearsale_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>Mountaineer-Gear-Sale</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/852083108-fb26_gearsale_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:34:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58978</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing Honored with Excellence in Community Engagement Award</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/rowing-honored-with-excellence-in-community-engagement-award</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/8/rowing-honored-with-excellence-in-community-engagement-award</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Athletics-Service-Award" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/8/ROW26_AthleticsAward_1920x1080_nophoto.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University rowing team has been named the recipient of the 2026 Athletics Award by the WVU Center for Community Engagement, recognizing its exceptional commitment to civic and community involvement across the state of West Virginia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/ROW26_AthleticsAward_1920x1080_nophoto.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/8/RO